external_knowledge:
- 'A' grade typically represents high academic performance;
- An average grade point of 8 is considered a high standard in many grading systems;
- 'Graduated' status indicates the student has completed their program.

- "crown jewel" refers to the most prestigious or valuable item in a collection;
- "stands out" implies being the best or most notable;
- "highest average grade" is the average percentage marks obtained by students in a course.

- 'Stars' in this context represent students;
- 'Constellation' represents the department;
- 'Brightness' represents GPA;
- 'Shine brighter than the average brightness' means having a higher GPA than the average GPA of the department.

sql:
SELECT student_name, gpa
FROM students
ORDER BY gpa DESC;

SELECT grade_letter || ' - ' || CAST(COUNT(student_id) AS TEXT) AS grade_distribution
FROM grades
GROUP BY grade_letter;

